# YearBook App (MVP Scaffold)

React Native + Expo app scaffold for capturing memories and exporting simple photobooks.

## MVP Included
- Create projects with a project type and optional thumbnail image.
- Select an existing project from the home screen.
- Create memories inside a project (each memory acts as a page/group).
- Reorder memories within a project (Up/Down controls).
- Pick photos from device library and attach them to a specific memory.
- Persist memories and photos locally with AsyncStorage.
- Generate prompt suggestions based on time interval since last memory update.
- Generate prompt suggestions based on sudden increase in photos added.
- Generate prompt suggestions based on presence of location metadata.
- Export all memories from a project into one PDF in project memory order.

## Project Structure
- `app/index.tsx`: project selection + create project flow.
- `app/project/[id].tsx`: project details, memory creation, memory ordering, project PDF export.
- `app/memory/[id].tsx`: memory details + add photos.
- `app/prompts.tsx`: prompt center.
- `src/context/AppContext.tsx`: app state + data actions.
- `src/services/photoService.ts`: image picking, local file copy, location fetch.
- `src/services/promptEngine.ts`: prompt rules.
- `src/services/exportService.ts`: HTML-to-PDF export + share.
- `src/storage.ts`: local persistence.

## Run
1. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```
2. Start Expo:
```bash
npm run start
```
3. Open Android emulator/device:
```bash
npm run android
```

## Notes
- This repo is currently local-first (no backend yet).
- iOS support can be enabled from the same Expo codebase when you are ready.
- Multi-user collaboration and advanced template generation are planned for a later phase.
